body:
On second thought, it does call 'checkBalanceChanged' immediately before starting or restarting the timer - so it won't be delayed, but might actually be a bit costly if a bunch of transactions come in very quickly. Perhaps it would be better to remove the call to 'checkBalanceChanged', and remove the condition that is there, and just check 'isActive' like you suggest. I.e.

// checkBalanceChanged();
if(!pollTimer->isActive()) pollTimer->start();

Would that make more sense?

